ost|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref> Beijing reported an additional five laboratory-confirmed cases, while Guangdong reported an additional nine laboratory-confirmed cases. Shanghai reported an additional five laboratory-confirmed cases, while Tianjin reported an additional two laboratory-confirmed cases. Zhejiang and Jiangxi reported an additional five and one laboratory-confirmed cases, respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.datanews.caixin.com/m/2020-01-20/101506236.html|title=\u5730\u56fe\uff5c\u4e2d\u56fd\u6b66\u6c49\u80ba\u708e\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b\u5b9e\u65f6\u52a8\u6001|website=m.datanews.caixin.com|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref>{{better source|date=January 2020}} [[Liaoning]] reported its first two laboratory-confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wsjk.ln.gov.cn/wst_wsjskx/202001/t20200122_3728428.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200222161515/http://wsjk.ln.gov.cn/wst_wsjskx/202001/t20200122_3728428.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=2020-02-22|title=\u8fbd\u5b81\u7701\u536b\u751f\u5065\u5eb7\u59d4\u5458\u4f1a|website=wsjk.ln.gov.cn|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref> [[Guizhou]], [[Fujian]], [[Anhui]], [[Shanxi]] and [[Ningxia]] reported one laboratory-confirmed case each.<ref name=\":103\" /><ref>{{citation|title=2019\u5e74\uff0d2020\u5e74\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72c0\u75c5\u6bd2\u80ba\u708e\u4e8b\u4ef6|date=2020-01-22|url=https://zh.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=2019%E5%B9%B4%EF%BC%8D2020%E5%B9%B4%E6%96%B0%E5%9E%8B%E5%86%A0%E7%8B%80%E7%97%85%E6%AF%92%E8%82%BA%E7%82%8E%E4%BA%8B%E4%BB%B6&oldid=57806349|work=\u7ef4\u57fa\u767e\u79d1\uff0c\u81ea\u7531\u7684\u767e\u79d1\u5168\u4e66|language=zh|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://wjw.ah.gov.cn/news_details_53898.html|title=\u5b89\u5fbd\u7701\u62a5\u544a\u9996\u4f8b\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b \u2013 \u5de5\u4f5c\u52a8\u6001 \u2013 \u5b89\u5fbd\u7701\u536b\u751f\u5065\u5eb7\u59d4\u5458\u4f1a|website=wjw.ah.gov.cn|acc