ebruary.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hotnews.ro/stiri-sanatate-23687251-primul-caz-infectie-coronavirus-confirmat-oficial-romania.htm|title=Primul caz de infec\u021bie cu coronavirus, confirmat oficial \u00een Rom\u00e2nia: Un b\u0103rbat din Gorj ce a intrat \u00een contact cu italianul care a vizitat recent \u021bara noastr\u0103|website=HotNews.ro|author=Neagu, Alina|date=26 February 2020|access-date=3 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226220952/https://www.hotnews.ro/stiri-sanatate-23687251-primul-caz-infectie-coronavirus-confirmat-oficial-romania.htm|archive-date=26 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mediafax.ro/coronavirus/detalii-despre-primul-roman-diagnosticat-cu-noul-coronavirus-are-20-de-ani-si-lucra-la-restaurantul-italianului-care-a-vizitat-recent-tara-noastra-18897127|title=Detalii despre primul rom\u00e2n diagnosticat cu noul coronavirus. Are 20 de ani \u0219i locuie\u0219te \u00een comuna Prigoria - UPDATE|website=Mediafax|author=Ficiu, Loredana|date=27 February 2020|access-date=11 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228181109/https://www.mediafax.ro/coronavirus/detalii-despre-primul-roman-diagnosticat-cu-noul-coronavirus-are-20-de-ani-si-lucra-la-restaurantul-italianului-care-a-vizitat-recent-tara-noastra-18897127|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Ecuador reported a suspected case of coronavirus, a Chinese citizen who arrived from Hong Kong.,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ticotimes.net/2020/01/27/ecuador-reports-first-suspected-case-of-coronavirus|title=Ecuador reports first suspected case of coronavirus|website=The Tico Times Costa Rica|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127172129/https://ticotimes.net/2020/01/27/ecuador-reports-first-suspected-case-of-coronavirus|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref> but the first case would not be confirmed until 29 February.<ref name=ecuador.1>{{cite tweet|user=elcomerciocom|number=1233773816825946113|date=29 February 2020|title=Ministra de Salud confirma primer caso de #coronavirus en Ecuador.}}</ref> Fiji authorities are holding six Chinese travelers in quarantine in [[Nadi]] as a precaution after they failed to gain entry to Samoa due to Samoa's quarantine requirements that were implemented Friday. The quarantine requirements, imposed after an emergency Cabinet meeting, compel anyone who's been in China to \"self-quarantine\" in a country free from the coronavirus for 14 days.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/world/2020/01/pacific-nations-on-alert-for-coronavirus-6-quarantined-in-fiji.html|title=Pacific nations on alert for coronavirus, 6 quarantined in Fiji|work=Newshub|access-date=2020-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127043627/https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/world/2020/01/pacific-nations-on-alert-for-coronavirus-6-quarantined-in-fiji.html|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref> In Poland, two children were admitted to the [[Krak\u00f3w]] hospital with the suspicion of coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://krakow.wyborcza.pl/krakow/7,44425,25638900,do-krakowskiego-szpita-trafilo-dwoje-dzieci-z-podejrzeniem-koronawirusa.html|language=pl|website=krakow.wyborcza.pl|access-date=2020-01-27|date=2020-01-27|title=Dwoje dzieci ze \u015al\u0105ska trafi\u0142o na dzieci\u0119cy oddzia\u0142 zaka\u017any krakowskiego szpitala im. \u017beromskiego. Wraz z rodzicami wraca\u0142y przez Pekin do kraju i zachorowa\u0142y|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127182321/https://krakow.wyborcza.pl/krakow/7,44425,25638900,do-krakowskiego-szpita-trafilo-dwoje-dzieci-z-podejrzeniem-koronawirusa.html|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref> In Mongolia a 14-year-old girl who was studying in China had fallen ill with a suspected case of pneumonia and laryngitis; she was pronounced dead on the same day. Health authorities have since taken a sample from the deceased girl to be analysed at the National Center for Communicable Diseases in [[Ulaanbaatar]].<ref name=\"auto3\">{{cite web|url=https://ikon.mn/n/1s32|title=\u0425\u044d\u043d\u0442\u0438\u0439 \u0430\u0439\u043c\u0433\u0438\u0439\u043d \u044d\u043c\u043d\u044d\u043b\u044d\u0433\u0442 \u043d\u0430\u0441 \u0431\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0430\u043d \u043e\u0445\u0438\u043d\u044b \u0446\u043e\u0433\u0446\u0441\u043e\u043e\u0441 \u0441\u043e\u0440\u044c\u0446 \u0430\u0432\u0447, \u0434\u044d\u044d\u0436\u0438\u0439\u0433 \u0425\u04e8\u0421\u04ae\u0422-\u0434 \u0438\u043b\u0433\u044d\u044d\u0441\u044d\u043d|last=iKon.mn|first=\u0413. \u04e8\u043b\u0437\u0438\u0439\u0445\u0443\u0442\u0430\u0433|date=2020-01-27|website=ikon.mn|access-date=2020-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127155037/https://ikon.mn/n/1s32|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref> Two Mongolian students returning from Taiwan to [[Chinggis Khaan International Airport]] have shown symptoms of high fever and rising temperature and were put into quarantine after landing in Mongolia.<ref name=\"auto3\"/> In Switzerland, two people were put under quarantine at the [[Triemli Hospital]] in Zurich; both had previously been to China.<ref>{{citation|url=https://www.srf.ch/news/international/corona-virus-auf-dem-vormarsch-verdachtsfaelle-in-der-schweiz-gemeldet|date=2020-01-27|language=de|access-date=2020-01-27|title=Verdachtsf\u00e4lle in der Schweiz gemeldet|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126220817/https://www.srf.ch/news/international/corona-virus-auf-dem-vormarsch-verdachtsfaelle-in-der-schweiz-gemeldet|archive-date=2020-01-26|url-status=live}}</ref> These cases later turned up negative.<ref>{{citation|url=https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/coronavirus_swiss-tighten-rules-to-help-stop-spread-of-china-virus/45518156|date=2020-01-27|language=en|access-date=2020-01-27|title=Two quarantined patients do not have coronavirus, confirms Zurich hospital|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127015652/https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/coronavirus_swiss-tighten-rules-to-help-stop-spread-of-china-virus/45518156|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Germany]], the first specific, global case of coronavirus being transmitted by a person with no symptoms has been reported. The originally-infected individual is from [[Shanghai]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sciencenews.org/article/first-case-coronavirus-spread-person-no-symptoms-found-germany|title=The first case of coronavirus being spread by a person with no symptoms has been found|first=Tina Hesman|last=Saey|date=31 January 2020|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200203054720/https://www.sciencenews.org/article/first-case-coronavirus-spread-person-no-symptoms-found-germany|archive-date=3 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/study-reports-first-case-of-coronavirus-spread-by-asymptomatic-person/|title=Study Reports First Case of Coronavirus Spread By Asymptomatic Person|first=Andrew|last=Joseph,STAT|website=Scientific American|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205163704/https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/study-reports-first-case-of-coronavirus-spread-by-asymptomatic-person/|archive-date=2020-02-05|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.statnews.com/2020/01/30/first-documented-case-of-coronavirus-spread-by-person-showing-no-symptoms/|title=First case of coronavirus spread by a person showing no symptoms|date=31 January 2020|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205163743/https://www.statnews.com/2020/01/30/first-documented-case-of-coronavirus-spread-by-person-showing-no-symptoms/|archive-date=5 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Transmission of 2019-nCoV Infection from an Asymptomatic Contact in Germany|first1=Camilla|last1=Rothe|first2=Mirjam|last2=Schunk|first3=Peter|last3=Sothmann|first4=Gisela|last4=Bretzel|first5=Guenter|last5=Froeschl|first6=Claudia|last6=Wallrauch|first7=Thorbj\u00f6rn|last7=Zimmer|first8=Verena|last8=Thiel|first9=Christian|last9=Janke|first10=Wolfgang|last10=Guggemos|first11=Michael|last11=Seilmaier|first12=Christian|last12=Drosten |author-link12=Christian Drosten|first13=Patrick|last13=Vollmar|first14=Katrin|last14=Zwirglmaier|first15=Sabine|last15=Zange|first16=Roman|last16=W\u00f6lfel|first17=Michael|last17=Hoelscher|date=30 January 2020|journal=New England Journal of Medicine|volume=0|issue=10|pages=970\u2013971|doi=10.1056/NEJMc2001468|pmid= 32003551|pmc=7120970}}</ref>\n\nSouth Korean health officials met with Korean life science company representatives to speed the development of a test.<ref>Chad Terhune, Dan Levine, Hyunjoo Jin, and Jane Lanhee Lee. (18 March 2020). \"Special Report: How Korea trounced U.S. in race to test people for coronavirus\". [https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-testing-specialrep-idUSKBN2153BW Reuters website] Retrieved 21 March 2020.</ref>\n\nIn the US, there were surging increase of warnings from its intelligence agencies toward the end of January and into early February. The then-acting chief of staff Mick Mulvaney began convening regular meetings. In early briefings, however, officials said Trump was dismissive because he did not believe that the virus had spread widely throughout the United States.<ref name=\":11\" />\n\n===28 January===\nChina's Supreme People's Court through a message \u300a\u6cbb\u7406\u6709\u5173\u65b0\u578b\u80ba\u708e\u7684\u8c23\u8a00\u95ee\u9898\uff0c\u8fd9\u7bc7\u6587\u7ae0\u8bf4\u6e05\u695a\u4e86\uff01\u300bin its official WeChat account vindicated Dr. Li [[Li Wenliang|Wenliang]] and the other 7 doctors and said they should not have been punished as what they said was not entirely false.<ref name=\"web.archive.org\" /><ref name=\":3\">{{cite web|url=https://asia.nikkei.com/Spotlight/Caixin/Rebuked-coronavirus-whistleblower-vindicated-by-top-Chinese-court|title=Rebuked coronavirus whistleblower vindicated by top Chinese court|website=Nikkei Asian Review|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> The Court further stated that  \"based on the difference in cognitive level, different individuals may produce different degrees of false information about the same thing. We should permit the law's to have certain degree of tolerance towards individuals. For example, in the case of the 8 persons being punished by Wuhan Police for publishing \"7 SARS cases diagnosed in the Huanan Seafood Market\u201d, if we mechanically applying the law, since the new coronavirus infected pneumonia is not SARS, by saying SARS has emerged we can indeed determine that is fabrication of false information, and the information has caused chaos in the social order. In accordance with the law provided, administrative punishment and even criminal punishment can be justified for the act of fabricating and disseminating false information. However, the fact is the message is not entirely false. If society had at the time believed those 'rumours', and wore masks, used disinfectant and avoided going to the wildlife market as if there were a SARS outbreak, perhaps it will help us better control the coronavirus today\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.caixinglobal.com/2020-01-31/after-being-punished-by-local-police-coronavirus-whistleblower-vindicated-by-top-court-101509986.html|title=Whistleblower Li Wenliang: There Should Be More Than One Voice In A Healthy Society|website=www.caixinglobal.com|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205002435/https://www.caixinglobal.com/2020-01-31/after-being-punished-by-local-police-coronavirus-whistleblower-vindicated-by-top-court-101509986.html|archive-date=2020-02-05|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/ETgXN6HInzlC8cxzhDdU9g|publisher=[[Supreme People's Court]]|script-title=zh:\u6cbb\u7406\u6709\u5173\u65b0\u578b\u80ba\u708e\u7684\u8c23\u8a00\u95ee\u9898\uff0c\u8fd9\u7bc7\u6587\u7ae0\u8bf4\u6e05\u695a\u4e86!|trans-title=Regarding the issue of authorities handling the new novel coronavirus as rumours|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202004701/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/ETgXN6HInzlC8cxzhDdU9g|archive-date=2020-02-02|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref>\n\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 8:<ref>{{Citation|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200128-sitrep-8-ncov-cleared.pdf?sfvrsn=8b671ce5_2|title=Novel Coronavirus(2019-nCoV) Situation Report - 8|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202195554/https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200128-sitrep-8-ncov-cleared.pdf?sfvrsn=8b671ce5_2|archive-date=2020-02-02|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThailand confirms six more cases, bringing the total infected there to 14. Thailand's health minister, [[Anutin Charnvirakul]], states that \"we are not able to stop the spread\" of coronavirus in the country.<ref name=\"auto11\">{{cite web|url=https://news.sky.com/story/thailand-not-able-to-stop-the-spread-of-new-coronavirus-11919860|title=Thailand 'not able to stop the spread' of new coronavirus|website=Sky News|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202160111/https://news.sky.com/story/thailand-not-able-to-stop-the-spread-of-new-coronavirus-11919860|archive-date=2020-02-02|url-status=live}}</ref> Singapore confirms two more cases, bringing the total infected in Singapore to seven. That was followed by a Hubei-related suspension from 29 January.<ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/wuhan-virus-7-confirmed-cases-in-singapore-no-entry-or-transit-for-new-visitors-with-hubei|title=Wuhan virus: 2 new confirmed cases in Singapore, bringing total to 7; no entry or transit for new visitors from Hubei|website=The Straits Times|accessdate=28 January 2020|date=28 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/