irus(2019-nCoV) Situation Report - 10|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131005409/https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200130-sitrep-10-ncov.pdf|archive-date=2020-01-31|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nWHO declared the virus was a [[Public Health Emergency of International Concern]] and advised \"all countries should be prepared for containment, including active surveillance, early detection, isolation and case management, contact tracing and prevention of onward spread of 2019-nCoV infection, and to share full data with WHO.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.who.int/news-room/detail/30-01-2020-statement-on-the-second-meeting-of-the-international-health-regulations-(2005)-emergency-committee-regarding-the-outbreak-of-novel-coronavirus-(2019-ncov)|title=Statement on the second meeting of the International Health Regulations (2005) Emergency Committee regarding the outbreak of novel coronavirus (2019-nCoV)|website=www.who.int|language=en|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n\nTibet confirms its first case, which was previously suspected.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wjw.xizang.gov.cn/xwzx/wsjkdt/202001/t20200130_131185.html|title=\u897f\u85cf\u81ea\u6cbb\u533a\u786e\u8bca\u9996\u4f8b\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e\u75c5\u4f8b_\u897f\u85cf\u81ea\u6cbb\u533a\u536b\u751f\u5065\u5eb7\u59d4\u5458\u4f1a|website=wjw.xizang.gov.cn|access-date=2020-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130000144/http://wjw.xizang.gov.cn/xwzx/wsjkdt/202001/t20200130_131185.html|archive-date=2020-01-30|url-status=live|language=zh-cn}}</ref> Cases have now been confirmed in all 31 provincial divisions of mainland China.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-china-51305526|title=Coronavirus: Death toll rises as virus spreads to every Chinese region|work=BBC News|date=30 January 2020|access-date=2020-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130030316/https://www.bbc.c