chive-date=2020-01-30|url-status=live}}</ref> This is the first confirmed case of human to human transmission within the United States.  Mr. Azar, Dr. Redfield and Dr. Anthony S. Fauci agreed that a ban on travel from the epidemic\u2019s center could buy some time to put into place prevention and testing measures.  Dr. Redfield said in an interview that \u201cThere was so much we didn\u2019t know about this virus,\u201d\u201cWe were rapidly understanding it was much more transmissible, that it had a great ability to go global.\u201d <ref name=\":1\" />\n\n===31 January===\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 11:<ref>{{Citation|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200131-sitrep-11-ncov.pdf?sfvrsn=de7c0f7_4|title=Novel Coronavirus(2019-nCoV) Situation Report - 11}}</ref>\n\nThe [[United Kingdom]] and [[Russia]] confirmed their first coronavirus infections.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2020/01/31/coronavirus-symptoms-britain-russia-who-wuhan-emergency/4620574002/|title=Britain, Russia report first cases of coronavirus as illness spreads to 20 countries|first=Doug|last=Stanglin|website=USA TODAY|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206103724/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2020/01/31/coronavirus-symptoms-britain-russia-who-wuhan-emergency/4620574002/|archive-date=2020-02-06|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-51325192|title=Coronavirus: Two cases confirmed in UK|accessdate=31 January 2020|website=BBC|date=31 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131100345/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-51325192|archive-date=31 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The first Swedish and Spanish cases were confirmed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/a/GGgL49|title=F\u00f6rsta bekr\u00e4ftade fallet av coronavirus i Sverige \u2013 kvinna h\u00e5lls isolerad|website=Aftonbladet|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201052456/https://www.aftonbladet.se/a/GGgL49|archive-date=2020-02-01|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/news/spain-confirms-first-case-coronavirus-222027208.html|title=Spain Confirms First Case of Coronavirus|website=Yahoo|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131232132/https://www.yahoo.com/news/spain-confirms-first-case-coronavirus-222027208.html|archive-date=2020-01-31|url-status=live}}</ref> The seventh confirmed case in the U.S. is in [[Santa Clara County, California]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://abc7news.com/5895060/|title=LIVE: Coronavirus: Bay Area's 1st case confirmed in Santa Clara County, CDC says|date=2020-01-31|website=ABC7 San Francisco|language=en|access-date=2020-01-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131215242/https://abc7news.com/5895060/|archive-date=2020-01-31|url-status=live}}</ref> A fourth case of coronavirus in Canada has been confirmed in [[London, Ontario|London]], Ontario.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nationalpost.com/news/world/coronavirus-live-updates-wuhan-virus-china-2019ncov|title=Coronavirus updates: Third case of coronavirus confirmed in London, Ont., bringing Canadian cases to four &#124; National Post|date=31 January 2020}}</ref> Thailand confirmed five more cases with the first human-to-human virus transmission inside the country of a local taxi driver, bringing the total to 19.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/wuhan-virus-thailand-first-human-coronavirus-transmission-12374356|title=Thailand confirms first human-to-human coronavirus transmission, total cases rises to 19|accessdate=28 January 2020|website=CNA|date=31 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131102023/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/wuhan-virus-thailand-first-human-coronavirus-transmission-12374356|archive-date=31 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bangkokpost.com/thailand/general/1847884|title=Human transmission of coronavirus confirmed in Thailand|accessdate=28 January 2020|website=Bangkok Post|date=31 January 2020}}</ref> Singapore confirmed three more cases, bringing the total to 16.<ref>{{cite web|title=Singaporean evacuated from Wuhan among country's 3 new cases of coronavirus, total now 16: MOH|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/wuhan-virus-singapore-new-cases-coronavirus-china-12373156|website=CNA|accessdate=3 February 2020|date=31 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201130127/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/wuhan-virus-singapore-new-cases-coronavirus-china-12373156|archive-date=1 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Chinese health experts warn the public that coronavirus patients can become reinfected. China starts repatriating citizens to [[Wuhan]].<ref name=\":15\">{{cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/society/article/3048320/china-coronavirus-deadly-day-hubei-record-high-42-patients-die|title=Coronavirus: Chinese health experts warn patients can get reinfected|date=31 January 2020|website=South China Morning Post|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205130515/https://www.scmp.com/news/china/society/article/3048320/china-coronavirus-deadly-day-hubei-record-high-42-patients-die|archive-date=5 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nA senior leader at US Department of Health and Human Services said staff members were sent to Travis Air Force Base and March Air Reserve Base in late January and early February and were ordered to enter quarantined areas were not provided with proper safety-protocol training or equipment, with at least one person staying in a nearby hotel and leaving California on a commercial flight. <ref>{{Cite news|last=Cochrane|first=Emily|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/27/us/politics/coronavirus-us-whistleblower.html|title=U.S. Health Workers Responding to Coronavirus Lacked Training and Protective Gear, Whistle-Blower Says|date=2020-02-27|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-04-14|last2=Weiland|first2=Noah|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331|last3=Sanger-Katz|first3=Margot}}</ref>\n\n===Summary===\nThe following is the list of countries and territories with confirmed cases during the period of November 2019 \u2013 January 2020 sorted by date of the first confirmed case(s):\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:5em;\"  | Date\n! style=\"width:25em;\" | Country or territory\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2 January\n| {{flagdeco|CHN}} [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic in mainland China|China]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|13 January\n| {{flagdeco|THA}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Thailand|Thailand]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|16 January\n| {{flagdeco|JPN}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Japan|Japan]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|20 January\n| {{flagdeco|KOR}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in South Korea|South Korea]] \u2022 {{flagdeco|USA}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States|United States]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|21 January\n| {{flagdeco|TWN}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Taiwan|Taiwan]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|22 January\n| {{flagdeco|HKG}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Hong Kong|Hong Kong]] \u2022 {{flagdeco|MAC}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Macau|Macau]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|23 January\n|  {{flagdeco|SGP}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Singapore|Singapore]] \u2022 {{flagdeco|VNM}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Vietnam|Vietnam]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|24 January\n| {{flagdeco|FRA}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in France|France]] \u2022 {{flagdeco|NPL}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Nepal|Nepal]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|25 January\n| {{flagdeco|AUS}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Australia|Australia]] \u2022 {{flagdeco|CAN}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Canada|Canada]] \u2022 {{flagdeco|MYS}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Malaysia|Malaysia]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|27 January\n| {{flagdeco|KHM}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Cambodia|Cambodia]] \u2022 {{flagdeco|DEU}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Germany|Germany]] \u2022 {{flagdeco|LKA}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Sri Lanka|Sri Lanka]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|29 January\n| {{flagdeco|FIN}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Finland|Finland]] \u2022 {{flagdeco|ARE}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Arab Emirates|United Arab Emirates]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n|  style=\"text-align:center;\"|30 January\n| {{flagdeco|IND}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in India|India]] \u2022 {{flagdeco|ITA}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy|Italy]] \u2022 {{flagdeco|PHL}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Philippines|Philippines]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|31 January\n| {{flagdeco|RUS}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Russia|Russia]] \u2022 {{flagdeco|ESP}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Spain|Spain]] \u2022 {{flagdeco|SWE}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Sweden|Sweden]] \u2022 {{flagdeco|UK}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom|United Kingdom]]\n|}\n\n== Events, reactions, and measures in mainland China ==\n====20 December 2019====\nOn {{date|2019-12-20}}, Winner Medical Group decided to cancel their executive meeting in Hubei.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.winnermedical.cn/cn/newsdetail/106/666.html|title=\u8fd9\u4e9b\u5929\uff0c\u7a33\u5065\u533b\u7597\u505a\u4e86\u4ec0\u4e48|date=2020-01-27|publisher=Winner Medical Group}}</ref>\n\n====30\u201331 December====\n\nOn {{date|2019-12-30}}, an \"urgent notice on the treatment of pneumonia of unknown cause\" was issued by the Medical Administration and Medical Administration of Wuhan Municipal Health Committee.<ref name=\"promed30dec\">{{cite web|title=UNDIAGNOSED PNEUMONIA \u2013 CHINA (HUBEI): REQUEST FOR INFORMATION. Archive Number: 20191230.6864153|url=https://promedmail.org/promed-post/?id=6864153|website=Pro-MED-mail|publisher=International Society for Infectious Diseases|accessdate=19 January 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"healthcomm\">{{cite web|author1=Wuhan Health Committee|url=https://www.nchrd.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/%E5%85%B3%E4%BA%8E%E5%81%9A%E5%A5%BD%E4%B8%8D%E6%98%8E%E5%8E%9F%E5%9B%A0%E8%82%BA%E7%82%8E%E6%95%91%E6%B2%BB%E5%B7%A5%E4%BD%9C%E7%9A%84%E7%B4%A7%E6%80%A5%E9%80%9A%E7%9F%A5.pdf|website=Chinese Human Rights Defenders|accessdate=14 February 2020|language=zh|title=\u5173\u4e8e\u505a\u597d\u4e0d\u660e\u539f\u56e0\u80ba\u708e\u6551\u6cbb\u5de5\u4f5c\u7684\u6025\u901a\u77e5|archive-url=https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:%E5%85%B3%E4%BA%8E%E5%81%9A%E5%A5%BD%E4%B8%8D%E6%98%8E%E5%8E%9F%E5%9B%A0%E8%82%BA%E7%82%8E%E6%95%91%E6%B2%BB%E5%B7%A5%E4%BD%9C%E7%9A%84%E7%B4%A7%E6%80%A5%E9%80%9A%E7%9F%A5.pdf|archive-date=26 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe Wuhan Municipal Health Commission also made a public announcement regarding the situation.<ref name=\":5\" />\n\nA famous police officer in [[Jiangning District]], [[Nanjing]] mentioned the BSL-4 laboratory of [[Wuhan Institute of Virology]] when commenting on the outbreak by expressing confidence on its technological power and ability to fix the incident.<ref>{{cite web |author1=\u738b\u6d77\u4e01 |authorlink1=:zh:\u738b\u6d77\u4e01 |title=\u6b66\u6c49\u8fd9\u4e2a\u4e8b\u513f\u5427\uff0c\u8981\u91cd\u89c6\u4f46\u4e0d\u8981\u6050\u614c\u3002\u56fe\u4e8c\u6700 - \u5185\u5bb9\u795e\u5668 |url=http://www.5ce.com/view/weibo/335e5de2-832b-ea11-8da2-20040ff9d71d |website=5CE.COM |archiveurl=https://archive.vn/20200301195009/http://www.5ce.com/view/weibo/335e5de2-832b-ea11-8da2-20040ff9d71d#selection-253.0-253.10 |archivedate=1 March 2020 |language=zh-cn |date=2019-12-31 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n====1 January 2020====\nHuanan Seafood Wholesale Market, the source of the initial pneumonia cases, was closed on {{date|2020-01-01}} for cleaning and disinfection.<ref name=\"promedmail\" /> On the same day, Chinese state news reported that Wuhan police interviewed eight residents for spreading \"misinformation\" referring to the new infection as another SARS and \"exaggerating\" the danger.<ref>{{cite web |title=8\u4eba\u6563\u5e03\u4e0d\u5b9e\u6d88\u606f\u88ab\u6b66\u6c49\u516c\u5b89\u67e5\u5904 \u80e1\u9521\u8fdb\u900f\u9732\u5185\u60c5 |url=https://news.sina.cn/gn/2020-01-22/detail-iihnzhha4048890.d.html |website=news.sina.cn |language=zh-cn |date=22 January 2020}}</ref> However, [[CNA (news channel)|CNA]] reported on the same date that Wuhan police said they had punished eight people for \"publishing or forwarding false information on the internet without verification.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/china-rules-out-sars-in-mystery-viral-pneumonia-outbreak-12235422|title=China rules out SARS in mystery viral pneumonia outbreak|website=CNA|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200106164940/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/china-rules-out-sars-in-mystery-viral-pneumonia-outbreak-12235422|archive-date=2020-01-06|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn {{date|2020-01-01}}, a genetic sequencing company was notified by the Wuhan Municipal Health Committee that further sequencing of novel coronavirus samples were no longer allowed, existing samples must be destroyed and all data must be kept secret.<ref name=\"caixintrace\" />\n\n====2 January====\nOn {{date|2020-01-02}}, [[Central Hospital of Wuhan]] banned its staffs from discussing the disease publicly or recording them using text or image that can be used as evidence; situation of individual patients can only be mentioned verbally when doctors change shift.<ref>{{cite web |author1=\u675c\u73ae |title=\u4eb2\u5386\u8005\u8bb2\u8ff0\uff1a\u6b66\u6c49\u5e02\u4e2d\u5fc3\u533b\u9662\u533b\u62a4\u4eba\u5458\u88ab\u611f\u67d3\u59cb\u672b |url=https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/1zNY2YXy75snzwX3Tg09Cg |website=mp.weixin.qq.com |publisher=\u4e2d\u56fd\u65b0\u95fb\u5468\u520a |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200217184406/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/1zNY2YXy75snzwX3Tg09Cg |archivedate=17 February 2020 |language=zh |date=17 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n====3 January====\nOn {{date|2020-01-03}}, China's National Health Committee Office published an announcement classifying the novel coronavirus as a highly pathogenic microorganisms (type 2), and request all the samples to be handed to provincial or higher level health authority, other organization or person with the virus sample should either destroy or transfer them and keep the log, and emphasis that all data must be kept secret and prior approval from the authority will be needed before any results can be published.<ref name=\"caixintrace\" />\n\n====7 January====\nOn {{date|2020-01-07}}, Chinese [[Paramount leader]] and [[Communist Party of China|Party]] [[General Secretary of the Communist Party of China|general secretary]] [[Xi Jinping]] raised demand on the prevention and control of the pneumonia epidemic caused by novel coronavirus in Wuhan in a [[Politburo Standing Committee of the Communist Party of China]] meeting, according to article published by himself in February.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.yahoo.co.jp/byline/endohomare/20200216-00163380/|website=Yahoo! Japan News|date=16 February 2020|title=\u7fd2\u8fd1\u5e73\u300c1\u67087\u65e5\u306b\u611f\u67d3\u5bfe\u7b56\u6307\u793a\u300d\u306f\u865a\u507d\u304b}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/02/17/asia/china-coronavirus-xi-jinping-intl-hnk/index.html|title=Did Xi Jinping know about the coronavirus outbreak earlier than first suggested?|date=17 February 2020|website=CNN|first=James|last=Griffiths}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cpc.people.com.cn/n1/2020/0216/c164113-31589205.html|title=\u4e00\u6761\u65f6\u95f4\u8f74\u7eb5\u89c8\u4e60\u8fd1\u5e73\u7684\u6218\"\u75ab\"\u65e5\u5fd7|date=17 February 2020|author=\u65b0\u65f6\u4ee3\u5b66\u4e60\u5de5\u4f5c\u5ba4|website=\u4eba\u6c11\u7f51-\u4e2d\u56fd\u5171\u4ea7\u515a\u65b0\u95fb\u7f51}}</ref>\n\n====10 January====\nThe gene sequencing data of the isolated 2019-nCoV, a virus from the same family as the SARS coronavirus, was posted on Virological.org by researchers from [[Shanghai Public Health Clinical Center]] and [[Fudan University]], Shanghai. A further three sequences from the [[Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention]], one from the [[Peking Union Medical College|Chinese Academy of Medical Sciences]], and one from [[Jinyintan Hospital]] in Wuhan were posted to the Global Initiative on Sharing All Influenza Data ([[GISAID]]) portal.<ref name=\"Schnirring13Jan2020\" /><ref name=\"Schnirring11Jan2020\" /><ref name=\"Gan9Jan2020\" /><ref name=\"NCBI\" /> The same day, [[Public Health England]] issued its guidance.<ref name=\"Schnirring10Jan2020\" />\n\nBeginning of the 2020 [[Chunyun]] travel season in China.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gov.cn/xinwen/2019-12/26/content_5464103.htm|date=2019-12-26|title=2020\u5e74\u6625\u8fd0\u4ece1\u670810\u65e5\u5f00\u59cb|work=[[People's Daily]]}}</ref>\n\n====12 January====\nHubei's provincial representatives from all over the province met in Wuhan until 18 January.<ref>{{cite web |author1=\u6e56\u5317\u65e5\u62a5 |title=\u7701\u5341\u4e09\u5c4a\u4eba\u5927\u4e09\u6b21\u4f1a\u8bae\u95ed\u5e55 \u6279\u51c6\u653f\u5e9c\u5de5\u4f5c\u62a5\u544a\u7b49 \u8868\u51b3\u901a\u8fc7\u300a\u6e56\u5317\u7701\u4e61\u6751\u632f\u5174\u4fc3\u8fdb\u6761\u4f8b\u300b |url=http://m.cnhubei.com/content/2020-01/18/content_12627775.html |website=m.cnhubei.com |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129162758/http://m.cnhubei.com/content/2020-01/18/content_12627775.html |archivedate=29 January 2020 |language=zh |date=18 January 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nShanghai Public Health Clinical Center, the facility that published the first genome sequence of the virus, was closed without reason.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/society/article/3052966/chinese-laboratory-first-shared-coronavirus-genome-world-ordered|title=Chinese laboratory that first shared coronavirus genome with world ordered to close for 'rectification', hindering its Covid-19 research|first=Zhuang|last=Pinghui|date=28 February 2020|work=South China Morning Post}}</ref>\n\n====14 January====\nReporters from Hong Kong being taken to police station after trying to film situation within Wuhan hospital.<ref>{{cite news|work=RTHK|url=https://news.rthk.hk/rthk/ch/component/k2/1502706-20200114.htm|title=\u6b66\u6f22\u6536\u6cbb\u80ba\u708e\u60a3\u8005\u91ab\u9662\u5b88\u885b\u68ee\u56b4\u3000\u672c\u6e2f\u8a18\u8005\u88ab\u5e36\u5230\u6d3e\u51fa\u6240|date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n====15 January====\nRepresentative from Chinese government and American government sign the [[US\u2013China Phase One trade deal|phase one trade deal]] over bilateral trade conflict in Washington D.C.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wearden |first1=Graeme |title=US and China sign Phase One trade deal, but experts are sceptical - business live |url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/live/2020/jan/15/us-china-trade-deal-trump-tariffs-global-risks-uk-inflation-business-live?page=with:block-5e1f53fe8f0852212f74eabc#block-5e1f53fe8f0852212f74eabc |website=The Guardian |date=15 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Donnan |first1=Shawn |last2=Wingrove |first2=Josh |last3=Mohsin |first3=Saleha |title=U.S. and China Sign Phase One of Trade Deal |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-01-15/u-s-china-sign-phase-one-of-trade-deal-trump-calls-remarkable |website=Bloomberg |date=15 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n====20 January====\nChinese premier [[Li Keqiang]] urged decisive and effective efforts to prevent and control the epidemic.<ref name=\"Premier urged2\" /> Beijing and Guangdong reported an additional three and thirteen laboratory-confirmed cases, respectively. Shanghai confirms its first case, bringing the total number of laboratory-confirmed cases in China to 218.<ref name=\"strait20jan\" /><ref name=\":6\" /> The investigation team from China's National Health Commission confirmed that the coronavirus can be transmitted between humans.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2020-01/20/c_138721762.htm|title=China confirms human-to-human transmission of 2019-nCoV, infection of medical staff|author=Mu Xuequan|work=Xinhua|date=20 January 2020|access-date=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n====22 January====\nThe government announced a quarantine until further notice, cancelling outgoing flights and trains from Wuhan, and suspending public transportation in Wuhan, effective 10:00 (02:00 [[Coordinated Universal Time|UTC]], [[UTC+08:00]]) on 23 January.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/22/world/asia/china-coronavirus-travel.html|title=Wuhan, Center of Coronavirus Outbreak, Is Cut Off by Chinese Authorities|newspaper=The New York Times|access-date=2020-01-22|date=22 January 2020|last1=Qin|first1=Amy|last2=Wang|first2=Vivian}}</ref> However, statistics compiled by the [[National Railway Administration|Chinese Railway Administration]] showed that on the same day approximately 100,000 people had already departed from Wuhan Train Station by the deadline.<ref name=\"Wuhan\">{{cite web|url=https://news.ltn.com.tw/news/world/breakingnews/3048974|title=\u6b66\u6f22\u80ba\u708e\u300b\u9ad8\u8abf\u300c#\u9003\u96e2\u6b66\u6f22\u300d \u5c01\u57ce\u524d\u5915\u81f3\u5c1130\u842c\u4eba\u9003\u51fa - \u570b\u969b|date=2020-01-23|website=\u81ea\u7531\u96fb\u5b50\u5831|language=zh|access-date=2020-01-23}}</ref> Furthermore, many Wuhan residents bypassed the checkpoints by taking [[antipyretic]]s, having seen tips shared on [[Sina Weibo]].<ref name=\"Wuhan\" />\n\nAt the day's night, Wuhan government announced that citizens must wear [[face mask (disambiguation)|face mask]] in public facilities.<ref>{{cite news|language=zh|url=https://chinadigitaltimes.net/chinese/2020/02/%E4%B8%AD%E5%9B%BD%E6%96%B0%E9%97%BB%E5%91%A8%E5%88%8A%E8%A2%AB%E5%88%A0%E5%B0%81%E9%9D%A2%E6%96%87%E7%AB%A0%EF%BD%9C%E6%AD%A6%E6%B1%89%E4%B9%8B%E6%86%BE%EF%BC%9A%E9%BB%84%E9%87%91%E9%98%B2%E6%8E%A7/|author=\u4e1c\u683c|date=2020-02-11|work=China Digital Times|trans-title=China News Weekly's deleted cover article {{!}} 'Li Xiangyi; Li Mingzi; Peng Dani; Du Wei (2020-02-10) \"The Regret of Wuhan: How China Missed the Critical Window for Controlling the Coronavirus Outbreak\" China News Weekly Issue 934'|title=\u4e2d\u56fd\u65b0\u95fb\u5468\u520a\u88ab\u5220\u5c01\u9762\u6587\u7ae0 {{!}} '\u674e\u60f3\u4fe3; \u674e\u660e\u5b50; \u5f6d\u4e39\u59ae; \u675c\u73ae 2020.2.10 \"\u6b66\u6c49\u4e4b\u61be\uff1a\u9ec4\u91d1\u9632\u63a7\u671f\u662f\u5982\u4f55\u9519\u8fc7\u7684\uff1f\" \u671f\u300a\u4e2d\u56fd\u65b0\u95fb\u5468\u520a\u300b \u603b\u7b2c 934'}}</ref>\n\n====23 January====\nWuhan [[2020 Wuhan lockdown|suspended all public transportation]] from 10 a.m. onwards, including all bus, metro and ferry lines. Additionally, all outbound trains and flights were halted.<ref name=\":7\" /> In Wuhan, construction began near midnight for a [[Huoshenshan Hospital|specialist emergency hospital]], modelled after the [[Xiaotangshan Hospital]] during the [[SARS outbreak|2003 SARS outbreak]] in Beijing, after it was proposed earlier in the afternoon. The new [[Huoshenshan Hospital]] opened on 3 February with a capacity of at least 1,000 beds.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.people.cn/n3/2020/0124/c90000-9651671.html|title=Wuhan to follow Beijing's SARS treatment model in new coronavirus control - People's Daily Online|website=en.people.cn|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200124140742/http://en.people.cn/n3/2020/0124/c90000-9651671.html|archive-date=2020-01-24|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe three provinces of Zhejiang,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3906959.html|title=\u6d59\u6c5f\u51b3\u5b9a\u542f\u52a8\u91cd\u5927\u516c\u5171\u7a81\u53d1\u536b\u751f\u4e8b\u4ef6\u4e00\u7ea7\u54cd\u5e94{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=24 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129211550/https://www.jiemian.com/article/3906959.html|archive-date=29 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Guangdong,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3908009.html|title=\u5e7f\u4e1c\u7701\u51b3\u5b9a\u542f\u52a8\u91cd\u5927\u7a81\u53d1\u516c\u5171\u536b\u751f\u4e8b\u4ef6\u4e00\u7ea7\u54cd\u5e94{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=24 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129211546/https://www.jiemian.com/article/3908009.html|archive-date=29 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> and Hunan<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3908499.html|title=\u6e56\u5357\u7701\u51b3\u5b9a\u542f\u52a8\u91cd\u5927\u7a81\u53d1\u516c\u5171\u536b\u751f\u4e8b\u4ef6\u4e00\u7ea7\u54cd\u5e94{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=24 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129211548/https://www.jiemian.com/article/3908499.html|archive-date=29 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> declared a level 1 public health emergency (the highest possible) in chronological order.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.guancha.cn/politics/2020_01_24_532969.shtml|title=9\u7701\u5e02\u542f\u52a8\u4e00\u7ea7\u54cd\u5e94 (Nine Provinces and Municipalities Enact Level 1 Responses)|last=|first=|date=24 January 2020|website=Guancha.cn|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200124100026/https://www.guancha.cn/politics/2020_01_24_532969.shtml|archive-date=24 January 2020|access-date=24 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe release of all seven major films for the Lunar New Year was practically cancelled.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://money.163.com/20/0124/07/F3KV962700259DLP.html|title=\u98ce\u4e91\u7a81\u53d8\uff1a\u4e03\u90e8\u5f71\u7247\u5168\u90e8\u5ba3\u5e03\u64a4\u6863 \u4eca\u5e74\u5df2\u65e0\u6625\u8282\u6863|last=\u7f51\u6613|date=24 January 2020|website=money.163.com|access-date=24 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200124052130/https://money.163.com/20/0124/07/F3KV962700259DLP.html|archive-date=24 January 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> In an example of [[black humor]], ''[[Plague Inc.]]'', which was released in 2012, surged to become the most popular app in China.<ref name=\"Plague, Inc.\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-51222796|title=Killer plague game tops charts amid coronavirus|date=23 January 2020|website=BBC News|access-date=24 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200123230821/https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-51222796|archive-date=23 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n====24 January====\nThe seven provinces, two autonomous regions, and all four municipalities of Hubei,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3909372.html|title=\u6e56\u5317\u7701\u542f\u52a8\u91cd\u5927\u7a81\u53d1\u516c\u5171\u536b\u751f\u4e8b\u4ef6\u4e00\u7ea7\u54cd\u5e94{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=24 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200125072914/https://www.jiemian.com/article/3909372.html|archive-date=25 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Anhui,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jiemian.com/article/3909516.html|title=\u5b89\u5fbd\u542f\u52a8\u91cd\u5927\u516c\u5171\u536b\u751f\u4e8b\u4ef6\u4e00\u7ea7\u54cd\u5e94{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|website=www.jiemian.com|access-date=24 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200125072916/https://www.jiemian.com/article/3909516.html|archive-date=25 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Tianjin,<ref>{{cite 